The paper proposes a supervised tensor embedding algorithm for high dimensional multimodal data with join decomposition of input and target variable. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories. The focus on human behavior data mining and prediction suggests that the paper may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of predictive modeling techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
